RACE.FOOTNOTES: PUGLIA stalked the early leader from the four path, launched a bid at he half mile pole, circled through the turn challenged for the lead at the quarter pole, battled with the early leader all the down to the last few jumps and prevailed. BE BO vied for the lead, took control an raced in the two path, set the pace, had a challenger drew near at the quarter pole, dug in an responded to encouragement, battled, could not shake the challenger and tired in the last few jumps but still ran a game second. SHEZA CAT was off in the middle of the field, raced on the rail, edged out into the four path at the three sixteenth pole, five wide in the upper stretch, raced in between rivals down the lane, battled, with three other foes for third, could not get up for third but out finished the rest. MUCHMORETHANREADY was off the pace early, raced in the three path, angled into the seven path and raced through the turn, had no kick in the stretch. OAK HILL SENIORITA mid pack, rail, mild improvement. RECLAIMED off pace, closed late. MISS CHARGE IT raced in the four, launched a bid at the three eighths pole, raced in between rivals and ran even. THURSDAY MORNING was off mid pack, steadied in the early going while jockeying for position, raced in the two path and settled, launched a bid at the three eighths pole, angled into the five path, was encouraged through the turn, responded well circling the field, raced between horses in the upper stretch, faded. HIGH ARABIAN was off slow, raced five wide down the back side, shifted into the eight path through the turn, was ten wide in the upper stretch, maintained. HALF SCOUT trailed through out.
